  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Diaspora connections: towards a policy framework for constructive engagement and reconciliation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) There is buy-in from the wider Sri Lanka diaspora community (in UK and other countries) and government  in Sri Lanka through specific line ministries to work towards a policy framework for diaspora engagement, 2) Diaspora members and political actors in Sri Lanka work together to draft a policy framework for diaspora engagement, 3) A Policy Framework for diaspora engagement is endorsed by cross-party MPs and  presented in the parliament for discussion, 4)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Lankan diaspora in UK, Canada and Australia, Sri Lankan Government, Sri Lankan civil society organisations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project builds on Alert&#x2019;s work over the last ten years in Sri Lanka, which includes working with multi-ethnic business leaders, faith leaders and politicians for peace initiatives to establish conducive conditions for inclusive local development, reconciliation and conflict prevention. The project will draw on the support of these strong networks across the country and established key connections with UK diaspora members that can be used to further build capacity and good relations.</narrative>
  </description>
